        spot_size = np.clip(np.random.normal(loc=mean_spot_size, scale=(spot_size_range[1]-mean_spot_size)**0.5)[0]  # Assuming a normal distribution around the mean for simplicity

        cutoff_energy = min(max_cutoff_energy, np.clip(np.random.normal(loc=mean_energy + np.random.uniform(-covariance_peercorrelation[1]*intensity, covariance_peercorrelation[2]*pulse_width), size=1)[0] # Considering the correlation with energy and pulse width
